    <item>
      <title>US RDA Vitamin D math mistakes cost the world about one Trillion dollars annually</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/us-rda-vitamin-d-math-mistakes-cost-the-world-about-one-trillion-dollars-annually/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 18 Mar 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/us-rda-vitamin-d-math-mistakes-cost-the-world-about-one-trillion-dollars-annually/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The US Institute of Medicine made 4 Vitamin D math mistakes in 2010&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The IoM finally agreed that they made math mistakes in 2017&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Instead of RDA = 600 IU, it should have been 8,800 IU (14X higher)&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;However, an IoM panel did not want to be embarrassed by publicly admitting mistakes.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The world copied the US mistake of 600 IU&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;$1 trillion math&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.who.int/publications/i/item/9789240017788&#34;&gt;Global health spending for 2018&lt;/a&gt; =  $8.3 trillion&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
