    <item>
      <title>SciAm - No benefit from more than 20 ng of Vitamin D (nope)</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/sciam-no-benefit-from-more-than-20-ng-of-vitamin-d-nope/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 22 Dec 2023 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/sciam-no-benefit-from-more-than-20-ng-of-vitamin-d-nope/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/attachments/d3.mock.pdf&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-file-pdf&#34; style=&#34;margin-right: 0.3em;&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;Download the Scientific American PDF from VitaminDWiki &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;National population sampling showed that most people were already getting enough of the vitamin&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;&amp;hellip;most people probably don&amp;rsquo;t need supplements&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;&amp;hellip;noting that the majority of the population is just fine at 16 ng/ml.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;&amp;hellip;Levels have actually risen since &lt;sup&gt;[2010]&lt;/sup&gt;&amp;rdquo;  Actually, levels &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/posts/4-reasons-why-vitamin-d-levels-are-crashing&#34; style=&#34;color: red; text-decoration: underline;&#34; title=&#34;This post/category does not exist yet: 4 Reasons why Vitamin D levels are crashing&#34;&gt;have fallen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Describes the failure of 4 trials that used too little vitamin D&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
